{"title_page": "11th Golden Laurel Awards", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Film producer award ceremony}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name          = 11th Annual Golden Laurel Awards\n| date          = {{start date|2000|03|02}}\n| location      = [[The Century Plaza Hotel]], [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| country       = [[United States]]\n| presenter     = [[Producers Guild of America]]\n| award1_type   = Best&nbsp;Producer(s) Motion Picture:\n| award1_winner = ''[[American Beauty (1999 film)|American Beauty]]'' \u2013 [[Bruce Cohen]] and [[Dan Jinks]]\n| previous      = [[10th Golden Laurel Awards|10th]]\n| main          = [[Producers Guild of America Award|PGA Award]]\n| next          = [[12th Golden Laurel Awards|12th]]\n}}\nThe '''11th Golden Laurel Awards''' (also known as '''2000 Golden Laurel Awards'''), honoring the best [[Film producer|film]] and [[television producer]]s of 1999, were held at [[The Century Plaza Hotel]] in [[Los Angeles, California]] on March 2, 2000.<ref>{{cite news|title=Laurels to rest on|url=https://variety.com/2000/scene/vpage/laurels-to-rest-on-1117779099/|accessdate=September 22, 2017|work=Variety|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923125026/http://variety.com/2000/scene/vpage/laurels-to-rest-on-1117779099/|archivedate=September 23, 2017|date=March 5, 2000|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Chuck|title=Producers Pick \"American Beauty\"|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/39496/producers-pick-american-beauty|website=E! News|accessdate=February 2, 2018|date=March 3, 2000}}</ref> The nominees were announced on January 19, 2000.<ref>{{cite web|title=Producers Guild of America announces nominations for Golden Laurel Awards|url=http://producersguild.com:80/awards/awards_2000_nom.html|website=producersguild.org|publisher=Producers Guild of America|accessdate=September 22, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20011215223247/http://producersguild.com/awards/awards_2000_nom.html|archivedate=December 15, 2001|date=January 19, 2000|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Golden noms named|url=https://variety.com/2000/film/news/golden-noms-named-1117761084/|accessdate=September 22, 2017|work=Variety|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923002629/http://variety.com/2000/film/news/golden-noms-named-1117761084/|archivedate=September 23, 2017|date=January 19, 2000|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Producers Guild of America announces winners of the 2000 Golden Laurel Awards|url=http://www.producersguild.com:80/awards/awards_2000_win.html|publisher=Producers Guild of America|accessdate=September 22, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010129045400/http://www.producersguild.com/awards/awards_2000_win.html|archivedate=January 29, 2001|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=PGA Award Winners 1990-2010 - Producers Guild of America|url=http://www.producersguild.org/page/PGA_Award_19902010|website=www.producersguild.org|accessdate=August 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Winners and nominees==\n===Film===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#abcdef;\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Theatrical Motion Picture|Darryl F. Zanuck Award for Outstanding Producer of Theatrical Motion Pictures]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top;\"|\n* '''''[[American Beauty (1999 film)|American Beauty]]'' \u2013 [[Bruce Cohen]] and [[Dan Jinks]]'''\n** ''[[Being John Malkovich]]'' \u2013 [[Michael Stipe]], [[Sandy Stern]], [[Steve Golin]], and [[Vincent Landay]]\n** ''[[The Cider House Rules (film)|The Cider House Rules]]'' \u2013 [[Richard N. Gladstein]]\n** ''[[The Hurricane (1999 film)|The Hurricane]]'' \u2013 [[Norman Jewison]], [[Armyan Bernstein]], and [[John Ketcham (producer-director)|John Ketcham]]\n** ''[[The Insider (film)|The Insider]]'' \u2013 [[Michael Mann]] and [[Pieter Jan Brugge]]\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#abcdef;\"| Norman Felton Award for Outstanding Producer of Episodic Television\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top;\"|\n*'''''[[The Sopranos]]'''''\n** ''[[Judging Amy]]''\n** ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n** ''[[Sports Night]]''\n** ''[[The West Wing]]''\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#abcdef;\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Long-Form Television|Norman Felton Award for Outstanding Producer of Non-Episodic Television]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:top;\"|\n* '''''[[Tuesdays with Morrie (film)|Tuesdays with Morrie]]'''''\n** ''[[The Century: America's Time]]''\n** ''[[Dash and Lilly]]''\n** ''[[The Passion of Ayn Rand (film)|The Passion of Ayn Rand]]''\n** ''[[Pirates of Silicon Valley]]''\n|}\n\n===David O. Selznick Lifetime Achievement Award in Theatrical Motion Pictures===\n*'''[[Jerry Bruckheimer]]'''\n\n===David Susskind Lifetime Achievement Award in Television===\n* '''[[Aaron Spelling]]'''\n\n===Milestone Award===\n*'''[[Sherry Lansing]]'''\n\n===Nova Award for Most Promising Producer===\n*Theatrical Motion Pictures: '''Robin Cowie and [[Gregg Hale (producer)|Gregg Hale]] for ''[[The Blair Witch Project]]'''''\n*Television: '''[[Aaron Sorkin]] for ''[[Sports Night]]'' and ''[[The West Wing]]'''''\n\n===PGA Hall of Fame===\n*Theatrical Motion Pictures: '''[[Robert Evans]] for ''[[Chinatown (1974 film)|Chinatown]]''''', '''[[Kathleen Kennedy (producer)|Kathleen Kennedy]] and [[Steven Spielberg]] for ''[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial]]''''', and '''[[Billy Wilder]] for ''[[Some Like It Hot]]'''''\n*Television: '''[[Marcy Carsey]] and [[Tom Werner]] for ''[[The Cosby Show]]''''', '''[[Jack Webb]] for ''[[Dragnet (1951 TV series)|Dragnet]]''''', and '''[[Quinn Martin]] and [[Alan Armer]] for ''[[The Fugitive (TV series)|The Fugitive]]'''''\n\n===Vision Award===\n*Theatrical Motion Pictures: '''[[Michael Stipe]], [[Sandy Stern]], [[Steve Golin]], and [[Vincent Landay]] for ''[[Being John Malkovich]]'''''\n*Television: '''[[John Wells (TV producer)|John Wells]] for ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]'', ''[[Third Watch]]'' and ''[[The West Wing]]'''''\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000531/2000?ref_=ttawd_ev_6 2000 PGA Awards] - IMDB\n\n{{PGAAwards}}\n\n[[Category:Producers Guild of America Awards|* 1999]]\n[[Category:1999 film awards]]\n[[Category:1999 television awards]]\n[[Category:2000 in California]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Film producer award ceremony}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name          = 11th Annual Golden Laurel Awards\n| date          = {{start date|2000|03|02}}\n| location      = [[The Century Plaza Hotel]], [[Los Angeles, California]]\n| country       = [[United States]]\n| presenter     = [[Producers Guild of America]]\n| award1_type   = Best&nbsp;Producer(s) Motion Picture:\n| award1_winner = ''[[American Beauty (1999 film)|American Beauty]]'' \u2013 [[Bruce Cohen]] and [[Dan Jinks]]\n| previous      = [[10th Golden Laurel Awards|10th]]\n| main          = [[Producers Guild of America Award|PGA Award]]\n| next          = [[12th Golden Laurel Awards|12th]]\n}}\nThe '''11th Golden Laurel Awards''' (also known as '''2000 Golden Laurel Awards'''), honoring the best [[Film producer|film]] and [[television producer]]s of 1999, were held at [[The Century Plaza Hotel]] in [[Los Angeles, California]] on March 2, 2000.<ref>{{cite news|title=Laurels to rest on|url=https://variety.com/2000/scene/vpage/laurels-to-rest-on-1117779099/|accessdate=22 September 2017|work=Variety|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923125026/http://variety.com/2000/scene/vpage/laurels-to-rest-on-1117779099/|archivedate=23 September 2017|date=5 March 2000|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Chuck|title=Producers Pick \"American Beauty\"|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/39496/producers-pick-american-beauty|website=E! News|accessdate=February 2, 2018|date=March 3,